item.title: Bitcoin mogul.... With a heart.
item.description: Sauce: https://www.threads.com/@sweetapple_ca/post/DRKhWAfCUYz More sauce: https://www.cryptopolitan.com/a-chinese-crypto-mogul-lost-millions-of-dollars-because-of-200-cats/ 'Employees told reporters that the stray cats appeared near the facility during the cold season in early October, looking for shelter and heat from the running mining machines. Within weeks, the number of cats had multiplied to around 200, transforming the crypto mining centre into an unintended feline sanctuary. Every time the animals slept on top of the machines, the graphics cards’ output was strained. This lowered hash rates and required expensive hardware upgrades. “It’s cute and touching, but these ‘beds’ literally cost us millions of dollars,” one employee told StoryTime, explaining that the animals’ presence caused overheating. Mining rigs turned into a cat inn The farm’s owner, described by workers as a lifelong animal lover, decided to accommodate them. “Luckily, the man who owns these machines is a cat guy,” said one worker. “He bought over 200 heating mats, and we’ve been instructed to put them in a separate room for the cats.”

item.title: Return of the Meme: 1528 (deep sea cod castle)
item.description:
Let's get this bread.
One of the things I miss the most from my jeep driving job was the Mexican food truck across the street. Best Tacos Al Pastor ive had outside of street food in Ensenada.
I keep having quasi-nightmares about the stupid computer system at work. About things that aren't even part of the system, if i actually stop to analyze them. Like, goddamn, I already have enough to stress about there, why the fuck are you adding onto it?
I played hookey from church yesterday to rest at home for a bit longer, then bottled and labeled another mead, emailed some paperwork, and did a bit of grocery shopping. I probably missed another cool bird at church this week (last week I saw a Townsend's Solitaire and I was sad I didn't have my camera), but so it goes.
I have two beverages left to bottle before probably putting the hobby on ice for a while, maybe indefinitely--need to save money for emergencies and maybe the sword. I made a Date Wine off a recipe for Table of Gods, a Mesopotamian cookbook in the process of being constructed, and I have my Basswood Mead, made with Basswood honey, aging on American oak, that I will backsweeten with more Basswood honey.
Hahahahaha
Hey look, it's my local dating pool.
I tried Magnesium Glycenate for the first time last night at the suggestion of one of you, and... well, there was a four hour stretch where I didn't wake up at all, which hardly ever happens. So maybe there's something to the suggestion, thank you.
Me, when I wake up at night still alive.
I mean, katanas are probably not the best zombie-slaying weapon, but that fit should otherwise work.
